&gt; In the collection framework when creating a sorted set a Comparator is
&gt; passed in as an argument.  If the Comparator argument is null the
&gt; compareTo() on the elements is called.
&gt;
&gt; I am not sure what use an assertGreaterThan( Collection, Collection)
&gt; makes much sense.   In mathematics it&#39;s not possible to say one vector
&gt; is greater than another, unless they are projected onto a given axis.
&gt; This is not really possible on your average collection of objects.
&gt;
&gt; I think the only two useful cases are...
&gt;
&gt; assertEquals(Collection, Collection);
&gt; assertEquals(Collection, Collection, Comparator );
&gt;
&gt; Passing in a null Comparator to the second method would behave like when
&gt; passing a Comparator to a sorted set, equals() method (or compareTo())
&gt; would be called on the elements.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Dave
